    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.10"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <add><note type="authorial">Department of Modern Languages</note></add>
                        <lb/>
                    The Commonwealth of Massachusetts   Southeastern Massachusetts University   North Dartmouth, Massachusetts 02747
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>25 January 1972</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Would I be overly presumptious in in asking you to inscribe personally (and date) the two enclosed works for me? Both books, <hi rend="caps">BLACK ELK SPEAKS</hi> and <hi rend="caps">A CYCLE OF THE WEST</hi> are read, reread, treasured, and greatly esteemed by me (and every member of my family). They both occupy a special place in my personal library and are respected as true, longtime friends.</p> 
                
                <p>To facilitate the matter, I've enclosed a stamped, self-addressed envelope. I'll respect your decision in either case, quite naturally.</p>
                
                <p>I fervently hope you are in the best of health and are continuing to write and create. In addition, I am still hoping that you will make a visit to these parts and be a personal guest of mine... Blessings on you, Mr. Neihardt.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>With my kindest personal regards, deep appreciation and steadfast friendship, I am</salute> 
                
                    <salute>Yours respectfully</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Melvin B. Yoken</signed>
                    
                    Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
